text: Jammu is the winter capital and largest city of Jammu and Kashmir, India. Jammu may also refer to: * Jammu (Lok Sabha constituency), Indian parliamentary constituency * Jammu (Tawi) railway station, in Pakistan * Jammu Cantonment, a cantonment in Jammu and Kashmir * Jammu district, a district of Jammu and Kashmir * Jammu Division, one of the two regions that make up the union territory of Jammu and Kashmir ==People with the given name== * Jammu Siltavuori (1926–2012), known as Jammu-setä (Uncle Jammu), Finnish child abuser and murderer ==See also== * Jammu and Kashmir (disambiguation) * * Jamu, an Indonesian traditional medicine * Jamu (disambiguation)
title: Jammu (disambiguation)
